---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import GeometryCanvas from '../../../components/diagrams/GeometryCanvas.svelte';
---

<Layout title="Triangles" lang="en" backHref="/explore-math/en/grade-7/" backLabel="← Grade 7">
	<h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">Triangles</h1>
	<p class="text-lg text-slate-600 mb-8">Triangle construction and congruence</p>

	<section class="prose max-w-none">
		<h2>When are two triangles the same?</h2>
		<p>Two triangles are <strong>congruent</strong> when they have the same shape AND size. But which information is enough to uniquely determine a triangle?</p>

		<h3>🧪 Experiment: Constructing Triangles</h3>
		<p>Drag the points and observe the congruence theorems in action!</p>
	</section>

	<GeometryCanvas client:visible />

	<section class="prose max-w-none mt-8">
		<h3>💡 Congruence Theorems</h3>
		<ul>
			<li><strong>SSS:</strong> Three sides uniquely determine a triangle</li>
			<li><strong>SAS:</strong> Two sides and the included angle</li>
			<li><strong>ASA:</strong> One side and the adjacent angles</li>
			<li><strong>SSA:</strong> Two sides and the opposite angle (careful: not always unique!)</li>
		</ul>
	</section>
</Layout>
